 Function :
    -------------
    1. It is a group of statements wrapped together to perform particualr task.
    2. Functions are classified into four types 
    	a. without returntype and without parameters
    	b. without returnType and with parameters 
    	c. With returntype and without parmeters 
    	d. with returntype and with parameters 
    3.Without returntype and without parameters 
    	syntax : 
    	void functionname(){
    
    	}
    
    	Example : Create a function show 
    			 void show(){
    
    		    }
    	Example : Create a method deposit 
    			void deposit(){
    
    			}
    			Execute :deposit();
    	Example : Create a method withdraw\
    			void withdraw(){
    
    			}
    			Execwithdraw();
    	Example : create a method display
    			void display(){
    
    			}
    	Example : Create a method create
    			void create(){
    
    			}
    	Example : Create a method invoke 
    			void invoke(){
    
    			}
    	Example : Create a method createData
    			void createData(){
    
    			}
    4. Without returnType and with parametes 
    	void functionName(parameters){
    
    	}
    	Note : Parameters are nothing but inputs 
    	Example :1 Create a method show with name and age as parameters 
    		void show(String name,Integer age){	// inputparameters 
    
    	    }
    	  Execution : show('Satish',33);
    				: show('Raghu',60);
    
    	Example :2 Create a method deposit with amount as parameters 
    		 void deposit(Decimal amount){
    
    		 }
    		 Execute: deposit(1000);
    				: deposit(4000);
    	Example :3 create a method withdraw with amount as parameter
    		void withdraw(Decimal amount){
    
    		}
    	Example :4 Create a method calculate with amount ,rate ,years as parameters
    		void calcualte(Decimal amount,Decimal rate, Decimal years){
    			Decimal intrest =(amount*rate*years)/100;
    			System.debug(Intrest);
    		}
    	  Execute : calculate(10000,2,4);
    
    	Example : 5 Create a method setData which will take industry as parameter 
    				if industy is Banking then set rating as Hot and ownership as public 
    				else rating is Warm and ownership as Private
    	
    			void setData(String industry){
    				if(industry=='Banking'){
    					rating='Hot';
    					ownership='Public';
    				}else{
    					rating='Warm';
    					ownership='Private';
    				}
    			}
    
    	Example : 6 Create a method calcualte which will take exp and city as Parameters 
    				if exp is more than 5 years or city is Hyd  then set salary as 50k and bonus as 5k
    				else salary is 30k and bonus is 3k
    	
    			void calculate(Decimal exp ,String city){
    				if(exp > 5 || city =='Hyd'){
    					salary=50000;
    					bonus=5000;
    				}else{
    					salary=30000;
    					bonus=3000;
    				}
    			}
    5. Method with returnType and with no parameters 
    	ReturnType methodName(){
    
    	}
    
    Example : Create a method show which will return name;
    		
    		String show(){
    			String lastName='Myla';
    			String firstName='Satish';
    			String name=firstName+''+lastName;
    			System.debug(name);
    			return name;
    		}
    		Execute : 
    		String  val =show();
    					 String :Satish Myla 
    
    Example : Create a method calculate which will return intrest ;
    		   Decimal calculate(){
    				Decimal intrest =(10000*2*4)/100;
    				return intrest;
    			}
    			Decimal val=calculate();// val=800
    
    6. Method with parameters and with returnType 
    	1. Create  method which will take age and exp as parameters 
    			if age is above 30 or exp is more than 5 years then set salary as 50k and bonus as 5k
    			else salary as 30k and bonus as 3k 
    			find the total of salary and bonus and return total
    
    		Decimal calculate(Integer age ,Decimal exp){
    			Decimal total ;
    			if(age > 30 || exp > 5){
    				salary=50000;
    				bonus=5000;
    			}else{
    				salary=30000;
    				bonus=3000;
    			}
    			total=salary+bonus;
    			System.debug(total);
    			return total;
    		}
    
    Example : void call(String name,String city){
    
    			}
    Execute : call(); //Error 
    : call('Satish'); // Error 
    : call('Satish','Hyd');
    
    Example : void invoke(String industry, Decimal amount){
    
    		  }
    Execute : invoke('Banking',10000);
